      "note_no": "1",
      "note": "The term al-bayan - denoting \"the means whereby a thing is [intellectually] circumscribed and made clear\" (Raghib) - applies to both thought and speech inasmuch as it comwises the faculty of making a thing or an idea apparent to the mind and conceptually distinct from other things or ideas, as well as the power to express this cognition clearly in spoken or written language (Taj al-'Arus): hence, in the above context, \"articulate thought and speech\", recalling the \"knowledge of all the names\" (i.e., the faculty of conceptual thinking) with which man is endowed (see 2:31 and the corresponding note 23)."
